President Barack Obama will award Corporal William "Kyle" Carpenter, a retired U.S. Marine Corps member, the Medal of Honor for his courageous actions in Afghanistan. Carpenter served as an Automatic Rifleman with Company F, 2d Battalion, 9th Marines and will be the eighth living recipient to receive the Medal of Honor for actions in Iraq or Afghanistan. He will be honored for his selfless service and bravery. Carpenter was born in Mississippi in 1989 and enlisted in the Marine Corps in 2009. He was medically retired in 2013 and is currently a full-time student at the University of South Carolina. The Medal of Honor is awarded to members of the Armed Forces who demonstrate gallantry and self-sacrifice above and beyond the call of duty in combat situations.